description: Try our easy to follow Chicken Stroganoff Pies recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
keywords: Stroganoff,Quick & easy dinner,High fibre,Nicky,High protein,Chicken pie,Low sugar,Chicken,Mushroom,Father's Day
name: Chicken Stroganoff Pies Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 2 sheet frozen puff pastry, partially thawed

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 200Â°C. Heat half the oil in a frying pan over high heat. Add onion and chicken. Cook, stirring for 5 minutes or until golden. Add mushroom, recipe base and 1 cup of water. Stir until combined, then bring to the boil and reduce to a simmer. Cook for 10 minutes or until cooked through. Remove from heat and stir in parsley.

Meanwhile, cut rounds from the puff pastry to cover tops of 4 x 1-cup-capacity dishes. Brush pastry rounds with remaining olive oil and place onto a lined baking tray. Bake for 15 minutes or until crisp and golden.
Divide stroganoff mixture between dishes. Top each with a pastry lid and return to oven for 5 minutes until heated through. Serve with salad leaves.
